While one woman claims her child was assaulted by staff at the ECD centre, another claims her child was throttled. CAPE TOWN - Western Cape Social Development MEC Albert Fritz has ordered a probe into claims of child abuse at a Manenberg Early Childhood Development centre.He's also condemned threats of violence against social workers who initially tried to investigate the matter.The department's action comes after the mother of a child at the centre lodged an assault complaint. The woman claims her child was assaulted by staff.Another parent claims her child was throttled.The department s Sihle Ngobese says, Our actions are guided by legislation, namely the Children s Act of 2005. It mandates the department to act in the best interests of children. The investigation will determine the course going forward. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)